.TH UPDATE 1 "January 2025" "dotfiles" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
update \- update package managers (homebrew, zinit, mise)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B update
[\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR] [\fB\-\-force\fR] [\fB\-\-manager\-only\fR] [\fB\-\-packages\-only\fR] [\fB\-\-all\fR] [\fImanager\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Updates package managers and their packages. Without arguments, presents a two-stage selection: first choose package managers, then choose update scope.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Preview updates without applying
.TP
.B \-\-force
Skip confirmation prompts
.TP
.B \-\-manager\-only
Update only package managers themselves
.TP
.B \-\-packages\-only
Update only installed packages/plugins/tools
.TP
.B \-\-all
Target all package managers
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help
.SH MANAGERS
.TP
.B homebrew, brew
Update Homebrew + packages
.TP
.B zinit
Update zinit + plugins
.TP
.B mise
Update mise + tools
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
update
Two-stage selection: managers then scope
.TP
update \-\-all
Interactive update scope for all managers
.TP
update homebrew
Update only Homebrew (interactive scope choice)
.TP
update \-\-manager\-only
Update only package managers themselves
.TP
update \-\-packages\-only homebrew
Update only Homebrew packages
.TP
update \-\-dry\-run zinit
Preview zinit updates
.SH FILES
.I ~/.local/state/system-update.log
.SH AUTHOR
dotfiles collection